  "prompt": "How do I get printouts of past IRCTC journey tickets?",
  "response": "To get printouts of past IRCTC journey tickets, follow these steps:\n\n1. Online Method:\n- Visit the official IRCTC website (www.irctc.co.in)\n- Log in to your account\n- Go to \"My Transactions\" or \"Booking History\"\n- Select the specific journey/ticket\n- Click on \"Print Ticket\" or \"Download Ticket\"\n\n2. Mobile App Method:\n- Open IRCTC mobile app\n- Log in to your account\n- Go to \"Booked Tickets\" section\n- Select the past ticket\n- Choose \"Print/Download\" option\n\n3. Email/SMS:\n- IRCTC usually sends ticket details to registered email/mobile number\n- You can retrieve and print from those communications\n\n4. Customer Care:\n- Contact IRCTC customer support\n- Request ticket reprint/details\n- Provide booking PNR or date of travel\n\nImportant Tips:\n- Keep login credentials handy\n- Tickets are typically available for 1-2 months after travel\n- Have booking details like PNR number ready\n- Ensure good internet connection\n\nRecommended: Always save digital copies for future reference.",
